\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b c}) Subsp. {\b prostrata} (Cosson) Dostál,{\i  loc. cit.} (1976) ({\i C. prostrata} Cosson, ?{\i C. amoi} Amo): Stems 20-30 cm, procumbent. Leaves grey-tomentose on both surfaces; lower lyrate or undivided. Involucre 6-7 mm in diameter, ovoid-cylindrical; appendages with a short apical spine, the lateral fimbriae 0·5 mm. Florets purple.{\i  Mountain grassland. • S.E. Spain}.
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b d}) Subsp. {\b boissieri}: Stems 10-30 cm, ascending. Leaves grey-tomentose on both surfaces; lower undivided or pinnatifid. Involucre c. 11 × 8 mm, ovoid-globose; appendages triangular-lanceolate, with recurved apical spine 3-5 mm, the lateral fimbriae confluent with the hyaline margin. Florets pink.{\i  Rocky places on mountains. • S. & E. Spain.}
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b e}) Subsp. {\b willkommii} (Schultz Bip.) Dostál, {\i loc. cit.} (1976) ({\i C. willkommii }Schultz Bip.): Stems 10-30 cm, ascending. Leaves white-tomentose on both surfaces; lower pinnatisect. Involucre c. 7 × 5 mm, ovoid-globose; appendages triangular-lanceolate, with a recurved apical spine 4-5 mm, the lateral fimbriae long. Florets pale pink.{\i  Dry grassland and calcareous rocks. •S.E. Spain.}
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b f}) Subsp. {\b pomeliana} (Batt. & Trabut) Dostál,{\i  loc. cit.} (1976) ({\i C. pomeliana} Batt. & Trabut): Stems 30-50 cm, ascending. Leaves green above, grey-tomentose beneath; lower undivided. Involucre 15-17 mm, globose; appendages with lower fimbriae confluent with the hyaline margin. Florets pink. {\i Stony slopes. E. Spain} ({\i S.E. of Valencia}). ({\i Algeria.})
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b g}) Subsp. {\b mariolensis} (Rouy) Dostál,{\i  loc. cit.} (1976) ({\i C. mariolensis }Rouy): Stems 10-20 cm, procumbent or ascending. Leaves green on both surfaces; lower pinnatisect. Involucre large; appendages with a slender, patent apical spine. Florets purple.{\i  Mountain rocks. • S.E. Spain} ({\i Sierra Mariola}).
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b h}) Subsp. {\b pinae} (Pau) Dostál, {\i loc. cit.} (1976) ({\i C. pinae} Pau): Stems decumbent. Leaves lanate on both surfaces; lower pinnatisect. Involucre 16-20 mm, ovoid; appendages with a short, recurved apical spine. Florets pink. •{\i  E. Spain} ({\i provs. Castellon, Teruel}).
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b i}) Subsp. {\b paui} (Loscos ex Willk.) Dostál, {\i op. cit.} 202 (1976) ({\i C. paui} Loscos ex Willk.): Stems 10-30 cm, erect; branches patent. Leaves usually green above, whitish-tomentose beneath; lower pinnatisect. Involucre 15-20 mm in diameter, ovoid; appendages large, with a recurved apical spine, the lower fimbriae confluent with the hyaline margin. Florets purple. {\i Calcareous mountain rocks. • E. Spain} ({\i Sierra de Espedan, N. of Valencia}).
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b j}) Subsp. {\b jaennensis} (Degen & Debeaux) Dostál,{\i  loc. cit.} (1916) ({\i C. jaennensis} Degen & Debeaux): Stems 10-20 cm, procumbent or ascending. Leaves white-tomentose on both surfaces; lower pinnatisect. Involucre ovoid; appendages with a recurved apical spine 5 mm. Florets pink.{\i  Rocky and open places. • Spain} ({\i prov. Jaen}).
\par
\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b k}) Subsp. {\b spachii} (Schultz Bip. ex Willk.) Dostál, {\i loc. cit.} (1976) ({\i C. spachii} Schultz Bip. ex Willk.): Stems 10-20 cm, usually erect. Leaves whitish-tomentose or -lanate on both surfaces; lower 1(-2)-pinnatisect. Involucre 12 mm, ovoid-oblong; appendages with a patent apical spine 5 mm. Florets pale pink.{\i  Hillsides. • S.E. Spain }({\i provs. Albacete, Valencia}).
