\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 132. C. monticola} Boiss. ex DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  7}: 302 (1838). Perennial. Stems 20-30 cm, erect, with long branches. Leaves lanate, more or less glabrescent; lower pinnatisect; middle undivided. Capitula solitary. Involucre 12-15 × 7-9 mm, ovoid; appendages with apical spine 2-3 mm. Florets pink. Pappus c. 1/4 as long as achene.{\i  Dry screes. • S. Spain} ({\i Sierra Nevada}). Hs.
